// Dynamically allocating Integer, float, character, double

1> Write a program that:

1.1> Dynamically allocates a single double variable.
1.2> Asks the user to input a value for the variable.
1.3> Prints the value of the variable with two decimal places.
1.4> Deallocates the variable.


#include<iostream>
using namespace std;

int main(){
    int *x;
    x=new int;
    cout<<"Enter a number: ";
    cin>>*x;
    cout<<*x;
    delete x;
    return 0;
}
